{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all retailers and businesses to accept cash for goods and services",
        "additional_details": "I would like the Government to protect the use of cash in society and safeguard the rights of consumers to use cash in shops and businesses.\r\n \r\nThe Bank of England has stated: \"the risk posed by handling a banknote is no greater than touching any other common surface, such as handrails, doorknobs or credit cards.\"\r\n \r\nAccording to UK Finance in 2019 cash payments continued to decline making 23% of all payments, totalling 2.1 million people.",
        "background": "Many shops and stores are using the pandemic as a way of moving all payments contactless, yet vulnerable groups such as the elderly and disabled rely on using cash for their everyday purchases. If this is allowed to continue we will fast become a cashless society.",
